---
import BlogPostLayout from "../../layouts/BlogPostLayout.astro";
import BlogByline from "../../components/BlogByline.astro";
import Icon from "../../components/Icon.astro";

// Make this page dynamic via SSR
export const prerender = false;

const publishDate = new Date("May 11 2026");
const readTime = "5 min read";

const isPublished = new Date().getTime() >= publishDate.getTime();

---

<BlogPostLayout
  title="Bi-Weekly vs Monthly House Cleaning: Which?"
  schemaTitle="Bi-Weekly vs. Monthly House Cleaning: Which is Right for You?"
  description={isPublished ? "Bi-weekly or monthly house cleaning — which fits your life? Compare costs, benefits & schedules for Huntsville, Florence, Nashville & Shoals homeowners." : "Coming Soon: Bi-Weekly vs. Monthly House Cleaning: Which is Right for You?"}
  noindex={!isPublished}
  publishDate={publishDate}
>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="pt-24 pb-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-900 via-gray-800 to-gray-900">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center">
        <span class="inline-block px-4 py-2 bg-[#FFA985]/20 text-[#FFA985] rounded-full text-sm font-medium mb-6">
          Pricing/Value
        </span>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold text-white mb-6 leading-tight">
          Bi-Weekly vs. Monthly House Cleaning: Which is Right for You?
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          {isPublished ? "Expert Cleaning Guide" : "Coming May 11 2026."}
        </p>
        <div class="mb-8">
          <BlogByline variant="dark" date={publishDate} readTime={readTime} />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main Content Toggle based on Published Date -->
  {isPublished ? (
    <article class="py-16 bg-white">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <!-- DIRECT ANSWER BLOCK - Critical for AEO -->
        <div
          class="bg-[#FFA985]/10 border-l-4 border-[#FFA985] p-6 mb-8 rounded-r-lg"
        >
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 font-medium mb-0">
            <strong>Quick Answer:</strong> Choose bi-weekly house cleaning if you
            want consistent upkeep for a busy household with pets or kids, and
            choose monthly cleaning if you keep a tidy home but need periodic help
            with deeper tasks. The right schedule comes down to your lifestyle,
            budget, and how hands-on you want to be between visits.
          </p>
        </div>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          Deciding between bi-weekly and monthly house cleaning comes down to your
          lifestyle, budget, and specific cleaning needs. Many residents choose
          bi-weekly cleaning for consistent upkeep, while others opt for monthly
          service to fit a more relaxed schedule. Whether you're a busy
          professional, a parent juggling responsibilities, or someone who simply
          values a pristine home, understanding how each option works will help
          you find the right fit.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">
          Understanding Bi-Weekly Cleaning
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-6">
          Bi-weekly cleaning means our trained specialists visit your home every
          other week. This schedule is a great fit for those who:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-600 list-disc pl-6 mb-8">
          <li>Want consistent cleanliness and tidiness throughout the month</li>
          <li>Have pets or children that contribute to everyday messes</li>
          <li>Prefer a more frequent, systematic cleaning approach</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          With bi-weekly cleaning, your home always feels fresh and inviting. Our
          specialists follow precise checklists so nothing is overlooked, and the
          consistent cadence means far less time spent on daily maintenance,
          freeing you to enjoy your weekends. If you're considering ongoing
          service, our
          <a href="/services/regular-cleaning" class="text-[#FFA985] hover:underline"
            >regular cleaning</a
          > plans are built around exactly this kind of dependable rhythm.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">
          The Case for Monthly Cleaning
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-6">
          Monthly cleaning is a solid option for those who keep a tidy home but
          want occasional help tackling deeper tasks. Consider monthly service if
          you:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-600 list-disc pl-6 mb-8">
          <li>Have a smaller household with minimal mess</li>
          <li>
            Prefer to handle routine cleaning yourself but need a hand with more
            intensive work
          </li>
          <li>Are budget-conscious but still value professional care</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          Monthly cleaning offers thorough, professional attention to detail. It's
          ideal for complementing your own cleaning efforts with professional-grade
          results that keep your home well-maintained over time. Our
          <a href="/services/house-cleaning" class="text-[#FFA985] hover:underline"
            >house cleaning</a
          > service can be tailored to whatever frequency works best for you.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">
          Pricing and Value: What to Expect
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          The Valley Clean Team provides transparent pricing tailored to your
          needs. Our bi-weekly service is priced to reflect the value of
          consistent, high-standard cleaning, while monthly service is priced to
          deliver maximum impact with less frequency and no compromise on quality.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          Both options are investments in your home's upkeep and your peace of
          mind. Our guaranteed service means you can trust that every visit will
          meet our high standards, ensuring your satisfaction every step of the
          way.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">
          Choosing the Right Frequency for Your Home
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-6">
          To decide between bi-weekly and monthly cleaning, weigh these factors:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-600 list-disc pl-6 mb-8">
          <li>
            <strong>Lifestyle:</strong> How much time do you spend at home, and
            how often do guests visit?
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Budget:</strong> What is your monthly budget for cleaning
            services?
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Personal preference:</strong> Do you want consistent upkeep,
            or are you comfortable with occasional deeper cleans?
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          There's no one-size-fits-all solution—it's about what works best for you
          and your family. The Valley Clean Team is committed to helping you make
          the choice that aligns with your lifestyle and expectations.
        </p>

        <!-- CLOSING CTA -->
        <div class="bg-gray-900 p-8 rounded-xl text-center mt-12">
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
            Reclaim Your Time—Book Today
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 mb-6">
            Whether you choose bi-weekly or monthly cleaning, our veteran-owned
            team delivers precision and accountability on every visit. Get a free
            quote with no obligation.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
            <a
              href="tel:2568261100"
              class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 text-lg font-semibold text-white bg-[#FFA985] rounded-full hover:bg-[#ff9a70] transition"
            >
              <Icon name="phone" class="w-5 h-5 mr-2" />Call 256-826-1100
            </a>
            <a
              href="/contact"
              class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 text-lg font-semibold text-white border-2 border-white rounded-full hover:bg-white/10 transition"
            >
              Request Quote Online
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  ) : (
    <article class="py-16 bg-white border-t border-gray-100 shadow-inner">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 bg-gray-50 rounded-2xl">
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-center">
          <Icon name="clock" class="w-16 h-16 text-[#FFA985] mx-auto mb-6" />
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4 mt-0">Article Coming Soon!</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 m-0">This article is locked and scheduled to automatically publish on <br/><strong class="text-gray-800 text-xl">May 11 2026</strong>.<br/>Check back then!</p>
          <div class="mt-12">
            <a href="/blog" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 text-lg font-semibold text-white bg-[#FFA985] rounded-full hover:bg-[#ff9a70] transition shadow-md no-underline">
              Back to Blog
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  )}
</BlogPostLayout>
